In commit "Interpret and validate rw_settings" (faec629663a92f28c5328ab3877ff58847bf9e35)

Would suggest just:

```c++
if (!flags) {
    LogPrintf("Ignoring unknown rw_settings value %s
", setting.first);
}
```

I don't think this can return false and prevent loading all settings when one has an unrecognized value, because it could break downgrading if allowed values are expan
